@eendebakpt 

Hello, I’ve fixed a few of the E501 issues and opened a PR for them. 😸 

Would adding a pre-commit setup (like ruff or ruff-format) be something the project is open to? It might help avoid these style issues in the future.

@Dr-Irv this change from `numpy.typing.NDArray` as `_: TypeAlias` to a `type _` (i.e. a `typing.TypeAliasType` instance), the [`check` function](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas-stubs/blob/b983c83b138f20222fee3d80d324ef1bf10e61a2/tests/__init__.py#L94) no longer seems to work (I'm guessing also at runtime).

A fancy solution would be to use `klass: typing_extensions.TypeForm` ([docs](https://typing-extensions.readthedocs.io/en/latest/#typing_extensions.TypeForm)) and then do something like `klass = getattr(klass, "__value__", klass)`. Replacing the `npt.NDArray` with `np.ndarray` in the `check` calls could also work. 

Is that ok for you? Reverting `NDArray` to a `: TypeAlias` is an option, but would only be a temporary one, since I'm planning on adding a second optional type-parameter for the shape-type to `NDArray`, which given their ordering will require us to use the new `type _` syntax either way.

