Rather than continue with our own SIMD solution, we decided to move to Google’s Highway as part of the C++ transition, as demonstrated by `nep-54`. However, NumPy uses a lightweight wrapper to eliminate Highway tags required by some intrinsics, and we also use modern C++ features. During the migration of new kernels, we may need to expand this wrapper. For this kernel, we need to wrap two intrinsics: `LoadNOr` and `ReduceSum`.

e.g. you can add `LoadNOr` under:
https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/489c0eae45f42587483eb5ee6db9e40c9b960297/numpy/_core/src/common/simd/simd.inc.hpp#L46-L52

